postcontent: The Benelli M1 semi-automatic shotgun based on the proprietary Benelli system, which utilizes the gun recoil and inertia of the moving parts to operate the action. This system was developed by Benelli by the mid-1980s, and is simple and reliable in operation. System utilizes the rotating bolt head with two locking lugs that lock into the barrel extension. The bolt is mounted inside the massive bolt body (bolt carrier), and fixed to it by the locking pin, which allows the bolt head to move slightly forward and back and rotate simultaneously within the bolt body. The massive inertia spring is interposed between the boldbody and head, and separate recoil spring is located in the buttstock, pressing the bolt body forward via the link at its rear. When bolt is in the battery, the locking lugs of the bolt head are engaged with the barrel and locked it. Inertiaspring, pressing on the both bolt body and head, holds the head in the forward position relative to the body. When gun is fired, it recoils and moves backslightly against shoulder of the shooter. Due to the inertia of the bolt body,it resists the initial recoil movement, so the bolt head, locked rigidly with the barrel and the rest of the gun, moves back relative to the bolt body,compressing the inertia spring and rotating itself to unlock due to the headlocking pin being encaged in the cam slot in the bolt body. As soon as the rotation of the head is enough to unlock the bolt head from the barrel, the residual pressure of the barrel pushes the bolt head back, and this, in turn,pushes the bolt body against the recoil spring, overcoming the bolt body inertial and commencing the reloading cycle (ejection of the spent case and feeding and chambering of the fresh round). As soon as the bolt group returns into the battery, the pressure of the compressed inertia spring pushes the bolt body slightly back against the bolt head, causing the bolt head to rotate and lock into the barrel. Now, gun is ready for the next shot. This sounds quite complicated, but the whole system is mechanically very simple and has few moving parts, resulting in high reliability and easy production and maintenance.No Trade

title: For Sale:  Blaser/Sig Sauer R93 LRS
postcontent:
This is a RARE German built by Blaser imported by Sig Sauer R93 LRS (Long Range Sporter) in .308 Win.

 This weapon system has many features such as a straight pull R93 bolt. I did change the factory thin cone shaped plastic bolt knob to an AI style larger round knob. It feels better in the hand and is much more easy to function when behind the rifle. 

It is fed by a TEN round magazine (TWO included). This platform allows for a quick change of barrels with just two allen bolts and can be done in just a minuite or two and do a barrel/caliber swap. Attached to the barrel on this rifle is the optional rare 20moa optics rail. 

The weapon is fully adjustable using the same allen wrench (included) for length of pull, cast on, cast off, height of comb, etc. The trigger shoe length of pull and weight is also adjustable. 

The aluminum chassis stock with very little plastic has many adjustments. The bottom of the forend is a full 1913 rail system.  Flush cups have been added to the left side of the stock. The barrel is 23.5" long fluted and threaded 5/8x24 for a brake or supressor.This is NOT assembled from misc parts this is a factory built rifle by BLASER.

Shipping is 35.00 CONUS for ground if you want insurance it will add 1% of the value.

title: For Sale:  NRA Daisy Red Ryder by Legacy Quest Outdoors
postcontent:
Brand New in Box. You can't buy these, they can only be won.

Gun is listed on GunAuction at:

http://www.gunauction.com/buy/12233975/bb-guns/2013-limited-edition-nra-daisy-red-ryder-colt-rra

After months of development with Daisy and Legacy Quest Outdoors, a special rendition on an American classic of the 1938 Red Ryder was created. This American-made Daisy model BB gun has a 17” stock and 11” forearm made of milled extinct American natural chestnut wood blanks. Legacy Quest Outdoors was honored to provide the American Chestnut wood for the 2013 NRA Special Edition Red Ryder BB guns. This historically rich material was procured from the Dominic Family Farm located in upstate New York. This circa 1930 large livestock barn was constructed with heavy Dutch influence architecture and is known as a bank barn. Bank barns were used by the Dutch to allow for heavy loaded wagons to be pulled into the loft for unloading and storage via a ramp that was built from the bank into the loft of the barn. This barn is an outstanding example of craftsmanship. It featured a hand pegged and hand hewn hemlock timber frame and was secondarily framed and sided in American Chestnut. The barn was dismantled and transported to North Carolina where Legacy Quest Outdoors crews meticulously hand selected and milled this high quality lumber for inclusion into this exciting project. Each board has been graded a total of 11 times to ensure that only the finest reclaimed American Chestnut was utilized. In keeping with Legacy Quest Outdoor’s passion to ’Pass it On’ the extinct chestnut stocks contain original nail holes and tight knots that provide originality to the item’s classic form. Each Daisy also includes recessed NRA gold seal medallion on the stock along with Red Ryder logo. Limited in production to 1,100, the Legacy Quest Outdoors Daisy BB Gun is truly collectible and available only at Friends of NRA.

title: For Sale:  Three Firearms For Sale! - S&W Model 19-3, Ruger New Vaquero, et al.
postcontent:
I have two lovely revolvers I am letting go to a good home! I need to move on to other projects, but after much deliberation and wanting to sell different guns than these, I have decided that hopefully these will bring someone else as much pleasure as they have brought me. I have priced them to hopefully sell quickly. I take firearm care and cleaning very seriously and have taken excellent care of them all! Please give me a call if you are interested! (918) 629-Zero31Five

1. Smith & Wesson Model 19-3 4" .357 Mag. In my opinion, the Model 19 has to be one of the best 'combat' revolvers Smith & Wesson makes (well, made). It definitely has a special place in my heart, and I always make sure I own at least one! Excellent Condition, locks up tighter than any revolver I currently own. The timing is perfect, it has been very well maintained, and I have fired less than 100 rounds through her (the majority of which were .38 special). Cleaned directly after each bout of target practice. Kept in a dehumidified safe for the entirety of her life. $500


2. Ruger New Model Vaquero 5.5" .45 Colt. My first foray into single-action shooting. In just as good if not better condition than the Model 19. The case-hardened frame still has it's new luster, the finish on the entire firearm is also immaculate. Again, less than 100 rounds fired through her, and thoroughly cleaned after each shooting session. Timing and lock up are VERY smooth and tight. Trigger pull is very enjoyable, and is the most accurate revolver I currently own (or maybe is just very forgiving on my broad-side-of-a-barn shooting skills!) Kept in dehumidified safe. $500

3. EAA Over/Under 12 ga. A no-frills double-barrel shotgun. It was bought new and has had less than 50 shells through it. What drew me to it was the 18.5" barrels, which causes it to handle like a carbine rifle and is extremely light. I originally bought it during my non-lethal phase I went through earlier this year! I thought that I would keep a non-lethal (i.e. rubber buckshot, bean bag, rock salt, etc.) shell in one chamber, and a very lethal shell in the other, whatever the situation would warrant! I even almost cerakoted the triggers blue and red to designate the two. I'm glad I didn't because that's not for everyone! I did install some fiber optic truglo sights on her that create a triangular sight picture that's pretty great to use. Anyways, it IS a quality over/under, finish is great, action is great, has hundreds of shells left in her. Can come with a couple of those specialty shells if you were so inclined! $200

All guns come with ammunition for target and self defense. Thanks for your time!
